reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I recently purchased the travel bottles, specifically because they are TSA approved for travel size. These containers have been a fantastic solution for my travel needs, combining functionality with a smart design.The silicone material of the containers is what initially drew me in. It's durable yet flexible, making it easy to squeeze out every last bit of product without any hassle. The fact that they're TSA approved is a huge plus. I've flown several times with them, and they've passed through security checks without any issues.Each container's size is perfect for short trips or even longer vacations if you're a light packer. They hold enough product for several days, yet are compact enough to fit in the smallest of bags. The flip top lids seal tightly, ensuring no leaks or spills, which is always my biggest concern with travel containers.The variety of colors is not just aesthetically pleasing but also practical, as it helps me easily identify different products. I use one for my face cream, another for body lotion, and a third for my hair conditioner.Cleaning these containers is a breeze - a quick wash with soap and water, and they're ready to be used again. The silicone material ensures they don't retain any residue or odors from previous contents.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Love that they’re all the same size, aesthetically colored, squishy and easy to fill. Used them for a cruise to bring on aloe, after sun, and surprisingly works great for baby powder. I use baby powder for dry shampoo and the containers make puffing the powder out very easy! Leak proof and work as designed!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Easy to fill and nothing spilled during travel. And the next day I was cautious but it still squirted out. :(
